               <head>Account of Maratha Wars</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2009200816 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064914 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3957-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Title lacking, endorsed on label attached to binding as <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Bhāʾo'nāmah</term> (<term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Bhāʾū'nāmah</term>)
                        </p>
                        <p>Untitled account of <term xml:lang="en">Maratha</term> wars from <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1171-1199</date> / <date calendar="Gregorian">1757-1785</date>
                        </p>
                        <p>Written by author in <name type="place">Benares</name> (<name type="place">Varanasi</name>, <name type="place">Uttar Pradesh</name>, <name type="place">India</name>), in <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1201</date> / <date calendar="Gregorian">1786-7</date>, for Governor-General Cornwallis
                        </p>
                        <p>Acquired by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7666" role="fmo">ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz</persName>, <date calendar="Gregorian">15 July 1891</date>
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
